// Task Synchronization
// Reads task definitions from task-graph.md or blueprint documents, builds execution batches
// via topological sort, and writes them into collab-state.json.

Tasks are defined in a YAML block inside markdown documents.
Batch structure: wave 1 has no dependencies, wave 2 depends on wave 1, etc.
Existing completedTasks are preserved across syncs; pendingTasks are recalculated as all tasks minus completed.

FUNCTION parseTaskGraph(documentContent) -> TaskGraph                            EXPORT
  Find the first ```yaml block in the document. Throw if none found.
  Parse line-by-line: each "- id:" starts a new task entry.
  Extract fields: id, files (inline array), tests (inline array), description, parallel, depends-on (inline array).
  Return { tasks: [...] }.

---

FUNCTION buildBatches(tasks) -> TaskBatch[]                                      EXPORT
  CALLS: detectCycles (task-sync), topologicalSort (task-sync)
  Check for circular dependencies via detectCycles. Throw with the cycle path if found.
  Sort tasks into dependency waves via topologicalSort.
  Convert each wave to a TaskBatch: id=batch-{N}, tasks with status 'pending' and dependsOn list.

---

FUNCTION topologicalSort(tasks) -> TaskGraphTask[][]                             EXPORT
  Build an adjacency list and in-degree map from task dependencies.
  Filter out empty strings and references to non-existent task IDs.
  Repeatedly find tasks with in-degree 0, collect them as the next wave, decrement dependents' in-degrees.
  Return the ordered array of waves. Throw if a wave comes out empty (cycle guard).

---

FUNCTION detectCycles(tasks) -> string[] | null                                  EXPORT
  Run DFS over all tasks. Track visiting (in current path) vs visited (fully processed) sets.
  IF a task is visited twice in the current path, extract the cycle as a subarray and return it.
  Return null if no cycle found.

---

FUNCTION dfs(taskId) -> string[] | null
  Inner recursive DFS function for detectCycles.
  IF taskId is currently being visited, return the cycle path.
  IF taskId was already fully visited, return null.
  Mark as visiting, recurse into each dependency, unmark and mark as visited on return.

---

FUNCTION generateTaskGraphYaml(tasks) -> string
  Serialize a list of TaskGraphTask objects back to the YAML format used in task-graph.md.

---

FUNCTION generateTaskGraphMermaid(tasks, batches) -> string
  Generate a Mermaid graph TD showing task nodes with short descriptions, dependency arrows,
  and wave-based fill colors.

---

FUNCTION getDocumentsPath(project, session) -> string
  Return the path to the documents directory for a session.

---

FUNCTION fileExists(path) -> boolean
  Return true if the path is accessible.

---

FUNCTION createConsolidatedTaskGraph(project, session, tasks) -> void
  CALLS: buildBatches (task-sync), generateTaskGraphYaml (task-sync), generateTaskGraphMermaid (task-sync)
  Build batches, generate YAML and Mermaid representations, compute wave summary.
  Write a complete task-graph.md document to the session's documents directory.

---

FUNCTION generateFallbackTasks(workItems) -> TaskGraphTask[]                     EXPORT
  Filter work items to code and bugfix types.
  Create one fallback task per item: id=item-{number}, files=[], description=item title.

---

FUNCTION syncTasksFromTaskGraph(project, session) -> TaskBatch[]                 EXPORT
  CALLS: parseTaskGraph (task-sync), buildBatches (task-sync), createConsolidatedTaskGraph (task-sync), getSessionState (collab-state), generateFallbackTasks (task-sync), updateSessionState (collab-state)
  Step 1: Try to read task-graph.md and parse tasks from it.
  Step 2: IF task-graph.md not found, scan for blueprint-item-*.md files and extract tasks from each,
    deduplicating by ID. IF any blueprint tasks found, write a consolidated task-graph.md.
  Step 3: IF still no tasks, generate fallback tasks from work items. Throw if none available.
    Write a consolidated task-graph.md from the fallback tasks.
  Build execution batches from all collected tasks.
  Preserve existing completedTasks from current session state.
  Calculate pendingTasks as all task IDs minus the completed set.
  Save batches, currentBatch=0, pendingTasks, and completedTasks to session state.
  Return the batches array.
